  "title": "Marketing Manager (East-5 days)",
  "description": "<h3>Job Vacancy: Marketing Manager</h3><h3>Industry: Service Industry</h3><h3>Work Location: Ubi, Singapore</h3><h3><em>(Near Downtown Line DT27 – approximately 10-minute walk)</em></h3><p>⸻</p><h3>Salary</h3><p>SGD 3,800 – SGD 4,500</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Working Hours</h3><p>Monday – Friday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Monthly Rest Days</h3><p>8 days</p><p>⸻</p><h3>About the Company</h3><p><u>The employer is a </u><u><strong>healthy food company</strong></u><u> operating within the service industry, focused on brand development, customer engagement, and market growth through digital and offline marketing initiatives.</u></p><p>⸻</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Manage and update content on social media platforms and the company’s brand website</p></li><li><p>Develop and implement comprehensive marketing strategies aligned with business goals</p></li><li><p>Plan, execute, and manage digital marketing projects, including social media, email marketing, and online advertising</p></li><li><p>Coordinate and organize promotional events and marketing campaigns</p></li><li><p>Monitor marketing performance and support brand growth initiatives</p></li><li><p>Perform other marketing-related duties as assigned by supervisors</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Relevant experience in marketing or brand management</p></li><li><p>Strong organisational and project coordination skills</p></li><li><p>Familiar with digital marketing channels and tools</p></li><li><p>Able to manage multiple marketing activities effectively</p></li><li><p>Good communication and teamwork skills</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Benefits</h3><p>Employment terms and benefits in accordance with Ministry of Manpower (MOM) regulations</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Contract</h3><p>Not specified</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Interview Method</h3><p>Video interview or On-site interview</p>",
